# LUFT Resonance Atlas (RF + Magnonics Scaffold)

This repository contains evolving experimental + analytical scaffolding to test a narrowband universal resonance hypothesis (base ~7468.779 Hz) across RF noise and magnonic / oscillator domains, with falsifiable controls.

## Key Features
- RF pipeline (peaks, harmonic enrichment, rational pattern matching)
- Magnonics scaffold (NumPy traces + meta)
- Phase alignment metrics (PLV, drift, empirical null)
- Harmonic & rational enrichment with empirical random-set p-values
- Config-driven (configs/default.yaml)
- Decoys: time scrambling, (future) frequency shift integration

## Quick Start
1. Populate WAV data: data/raw/HDSDR_*.wav
2. Run RF pipeline:
   python -m luftkit.pipeline --config configs/default.yaml
3. (Optional) Magnonics test:
   python -m luftkit.pipeline_magnonics --config configs/default.yaml --magnonics_dir data/raw/magnonics/test_run

Outputs: docs/reports/<timestamp>/

## Next Steps
- Add drift tracking per run
- Integrate frequency shift decoy
- Add amplitude falloff fit (1/n^α)
- Expand empirical null for PSD max distribution

## Philosophy
Unification concepts are expressed as measurable residual stability, cross-domain coherence, and lattice enrichment statistics (see docs/UNIFICATION_BRIDGE.md).

Contributions / iterations welcome. Preregister parameters before large‑scale claims.
